    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nLet's say I want to override highlight group Foo, which I'd like to be like Bar, but with italics. The following snippet:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"Foo\", { link = \"Bar\", italic = true })\r\n```\r\nis accepted by neovim (no errors on startup), but visually Foo is still the same as Bar (although `hi Foo` gives `cterm=italic gui=italic links to Bar`). \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFoo will visually look like Bar but with italic.",
    "closed_at": "2024-08-14T07:00:25Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That's just how highlights work; ypu are setting two properties (link and italics), and the forst overrides the second. Either olay around with \"combine\" properties, or -- better yet -- use the get_hl method, modify the return table, and pass the modfied table. ",
